text: September unemployment rates ranged from 1.6% in MD to 5.4% in NV.
Eight states and DC saw house prices fall between Q2 2022 and Q2 2023.
Real state GDP in Q1 2023 was higher than in Q1 2022 in all states except CT and IN.
September average private weekly earnings in states ranged from $897 in MS to $1,369 in WA.
Real manufacturing GDP growth Q1 2022 and Q1 2023 ranged from -6.8% in AK to 2.1% in NV and TX.
Public education jobs in September 2023 were at or above 2019 levels in 25 states.
MD, PA, and RI saw historic lows in unemployment in September 2023.
In Q2 2023, AZ’s year-over-year house prices declined for the first time since Q4 2011.
Leisure and hospitality jobs in September 2023 were above 2019 levels in 28 states.
Four states saw lower real retail GDP levels in Q1 2023 than Q1 2005: CT, NH, RI, and WV.
